name: Trucker
description:
Used as a foundation for heavy Scavenger tech. A serious cabin for serious survivors.

Great tonnage and an imposing profile, yet low speed.

name: Growl
description:
A completely stripped cabin with undying popularity among Lunatics and their disciples.

Maximum speed yet very low tonnage.

name: Wyvern
description:
A cabin that once belonged to a plane. It won't fly again, but it's perfect for fast battles.
Suits most combat situations. And the narrow profiles unlocks rich tactical possibilities.

name: WWT1
description:
Fairly durable and reliable. And how stylish!

A balanced cabin with enhanced tonnage.

name: Docker
description:
Cabin from a small truck for survivors who value reliability.

Great tonnage, but low speed.

name: Huntsman
description:
A light and fast cabin that you can often see in the Wasteland.

Performs well in most combat situations.

name: Jawbreaker
description:
Low profile and stern exterior that clearly point to its military heritage.

A balanced cabin with a low profile, but its speed leaves much to be desired.

name: Humpback
description:
The biggest cabin in the Wasteland. This time size definitely matters.

Incredible tonnage and wide profile yet low speed.

name: Carapace
description:
A tank is a tank even when the world is ashes.

High characteristics and comfortable size, but very low speed.

name: Duster
description:
A good example of using old scrap and a lawnmower to build a cabin suitable for survival in the Wasteland.

High speed yet minimal tonnage.

name: Fury
description:
Cabin of a military offroad vehicle. The name perfectly matches the appearance.

A multipurpose cabin with a low profile.

name: Bear
description:
This pickup has survived so many modifications that it looks like an armored car.

A multi-purpose cabin with low speed yet high durability.

name: Thug
description: A special version of the pickup cabin. Protective coating reduces the driver's chances of growing a third leg by 10%!

name: Quantum
description: Control compartment of an experimental flying vessel, re-tooled for moving along planet surface.

name: Pilgrim
description: Cabin from a multi-functional research vehicle, re-tooled as a base for an armored vehicle.

name: Steppe spider
description: Built using blueprints from a war hero, who had spent several weeks in the Wasteland and returned in one piece.

name: Icebox
description: These cabins used to be a key attribute in the rituals of the Frost sect. Inside, they maintained sub-zero temperatures and played loud, dramatic music. But if you throw out all the extra bits, there is enough room for armor and additional equipment.

name: Cerberus
description: The Cerberus cabin is a survivor's best friend. It understands everything, but just can't speak. Guts enemies in melee combat like the fierce mythical hound.

name: Bat
description: One of the Firestarter cabins carried across the Wasteland by the night itself.

name: Werewolf
description: With a cabin like this, a defeat can turn into a victory! And it does not fear silver bullets.

name: Jockey
description: Despite a somewhat awkward appearance and many patches on the hood, this cabin can pleasantly surprise you.

name: Hot Rod
description:
A classic that has lived through dozens of modifications, perfect for surviving tough conditions in style.

A multi-purpose cabin with good speed and small size.

name: Tusk
description: Several tusks fixed on this cabin's front are not only an element of intimidation, but also an unusual melee weapon.

name: Ghost
description: Once this cabin belonged to a helicopter and climbed high in the sky. It's just as hard to believe, as the fact that TVs kill people. However, all of this is true.

name: Torero
description: This cabin from a powerful supercar is equipped with a mighty engine and a couple of tech solutions increasing accuracy.

name: Favorite
description:
A prototype stolen straight from the factory and amateurishly modified a couple of times to take part in illegal races.

A versatile cabin with good speed.
